oient accept√©es ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_XCJWGELFVD'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XCJWGELFVD\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.567\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XCJWGELFVD\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.497\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XCJWGELFVD\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.852\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XCJWGELFVD\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.912\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q8-hint', 'Calculez \\\\( 1 - P(X=0) - P(X=1) \\\\) avec la loi binomiale.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q8-expl', 'On applique \\\\( P(X\\\\geq2) = 1 - P(X=0) - P(X=1) \\\\) avec la distribution binomiale pour obtenir environ \\\\(0.497\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q8-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q8-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 9\n\nUn organisme international organise une √©lection avec \\\\(3\\\\) candidats. Chaque votant choisit ind√©pendamment un candidat avec une probabilit√© de \\\\(0.4\\\\) pour le premier candidat, \\\\(0.25\\\\) pour le deuxi√®me et \\\\(0.35\\\\) pour le trois√®me candidat. Quelle est la probabilit√© que le premier candidat obtienne exactement \\\\(5\\\\) votes sur \\\\(10\\\\) ?\